        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 12:18PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 1218 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles west of Owyhee, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Owyhee and Sheep Creek Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
